# Cloudflare and Alchemy

The root `alchemy.run.ts` owns desired state for a preview-only
`Cloudflare.Website.Vite` resource. Alchemy remote state and Cloudflare provider
state remain authoritative for live identity and must be read just in time.

The scaffold deliberately owns no production zone, DNS route, secret, deployment
workflow, or mutation runbook. Adding any of those requires an authority decision,
runbook with rollback/revocation, provider readback, critical journey, and proof
packet. The selected Alchemy beta is recorded in `repo-structure.render.json`;
upgrades require a new compatibility epoch and full fixture verification.
